        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/77446228?v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">Request for Mozilla Position on an Emerging Web Specification</h2>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Specification title:<br>\nVoiceIsolation constraint</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Specification or proposal URL (if available):</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Explainer URL (if available):</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><a href=\"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-extensions/#voiceisolation-constraint\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-extensions/#voiceisolation-constraint</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Proposal author(s) (<code class=\"notranslate\">@</code>-mention GitHub accounts):<br>\n<a class=\"user-mention notranslate\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/users/perahgren/hovercard\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/perahgren\">@perahgren</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>",
            "url": "https://github.com/mozilla/standards-positions/issues/982",
            "title": "VoiceIsolation constraint",
            "date_modified": "2024-02-05T16:46:50.000Z",
            "date_published": "2024-02-02T23:11:32.000Z",
            "author": {
                "name": "perahgren",
                "url": "https://github.com/perahgren"
            }
        },
        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/67641?u=adea16237836e526afa569daa66747dacb79c56d&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/><p dir=\"auto\">Without a label on the left-hand column, it's not <em>completely</em> obvious that the expand button operates the way it does.  Also, the fact that we add another column is surprising when you are using a screen reader - the new content tends not to be presented automatically as a result.</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">We could experiment with <code class=\"notranslate\">&lt;details&gt;</code> here, but the fact that we have a table makes that somewhat difficult to get visual styling right.</p>",
