        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/32557109?v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/><h2 dir=\"auto\">Request for Mozilla Position on an Emerging Web Specification</h2>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>Specification title: CSS dynamic-range-limit proeprty</li>\n<li>Explainer URL (if available): <a href=\"https://github.com/ccameron-chromium/hdr-headroom-limit/blob/main/EXPLAINER.md\">https://github.com/ccameron-chromium/hdr-headroom-limit/blob/main/EXPLAINER.md</a></li>\n<li>Proposal author(s) (<code class=\"notranslate\">@</code>-mention GitHub accounts): <a class=\"user-mention notranslate\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/users/ccameron-chromium/hovercard\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/ccameron-chromium\">@ccameron-chromium</a></li>\n<li>Mozillians who can provide input (optional):</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Other information</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">This API provides a mechanism for imposing a brightness limit on HDR content. This has been frequently requested by image gallery apps.</p>",
