            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6678407?v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">Request for Mozilla Position on an Emerging Web Specification</h2>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>Specification title: WebSocketStream</li>\n<li>Specification or proposal URL (if available): <a href=\"https://whatpr.org/websockets/48.html#the-websocketstream-interface\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://whatpr.org/websockets/48.html#the-websocketstream-interface</a></li>\n<li>Explainer URL (if available): <a href=\"https://github.com/ricea/websocketstream-explainer/blob/master/README.md\">https://github.com/ricea/websocketstream-explainer/blob/master/README.md</a></li>\n<li>Proposal author(s) (<code class=\"notranslate\">@</code>-mention GitHub accounts): <a class=\"user-mention notranslate\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/users/ricea/hovercard\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/ricea\">@ricea</a></li>\n<li>Caniuse.com URL (optional):</li>\n<li>Bugzilla URL (optional):</li>\n<li>Mozillians who can provide input (optional):</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Other information</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">WebSocketStream is a new API for <a href=\"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6455\" rel=\"nofollow\">the WebSocket protocol</a> that enables backpressure by integrating with Streams. The benefits are better behaviour when one side cannot keep up with the data rate, and a more modern API.</p>",
